description.narrative: Despite the challenges of COVID-19 and the subsequent reduction in access and footprint, UNICEF continues to deliver quality and effective humanitarian assistance linked to resilience and development programming to the most vulnerable and marginalised communities, reaching 850,000 to 1.3 million people with WASH, nutrition and health services respectively. In 2020, UNICEF strengthened the efficacy and timeliness of humanitarian program planning by continuously assessing risk to communities and impact on services. UNICEF continues to lead and advocate interagency efforts with the aim of providing a protective environment for children and empowering communities. | Status:Met | As-of Date:12/01/2021
